    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is a surgical instrument of German engineering, preserved in true concours condition. At its heart lies the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, featuring Variocam Plus timing for a seamless power band and a visceral induction note. The critical IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear-main seal is bone dry. Power is delivered via a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle to the rear wheels, enhanced by a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by a corner-balanced Bilstein PSS10 coilover suite, significantly reducing unsprung weight and body roll without compromising compliance. Wrapped in fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber on lightweight BBS wheels, the lateral grip and steering feedback are telepathic. Zero bore scoring, impeccable paint depth, and a cabin that retains its factory-fresh matte finish. This is a turn-key collector-grade example for the discerning driver.",
      "price": 46500.0,
